items.name: Suspicious-Activity-Detection-Using-Pose-Detection-Blazepose-and-Machine-Learning
items.description: Machine Learning Pose Detection Framework for Suspicious Activity Detection

items.name: MLPro
items.description: MLPro - The Integrative Middleware Framework for Standardized Machine Learning in Python

items.name: onnx-model
items.description: ONNX (Open Neural Network Exchange) is an open standard format for representing machine learning models. It was developed by Microsoft and Facebook to allow AI models trained in one framework to be used in another.

items.name: AI-Enabled-Water-Resource-Crop-Selection-Framework-for-Climate-Adaptive-Farming
items.description: ChatGPT said:  An AI-driven framework that optimizes crop selection and water management using climate, soil, and rainfall data. It leverages machine learning to recommend sustainable, region-specific crops and predict water availability, promoting climate-resilient and resource-efficient farming practices.

items.name: E-HSE-Entropy-Guided-Hybrid-Stacking-Ensemble-for-PCOS-Detection
items.description: This project implements an Entropy-Guided Hybrid Stacking Ensemble (E-HSE) framework for accurate and explainable Polycystic Ovary Syndrome (PCOS) detection. The model combines advanced machine learning techniques with dual explainability mechanisms to provide clinically interpretable predictions.

items.name: pennylane-qulacs
items.description: The PennyLane-Qulacs plugin integrates the Qulacs quantum computing framework with PennyLane's quantum machine learning capabilities.

items.name: Image-Segmentation
items.description: A Novel Image Segmentation Framework using Adaptive Region-based  Unsupervised Machine Learning Mechanism

items.name: MLPro
items.description: MLPro - The Integrative Middleware Framework for Standardized Machine Learning in Python

items.name: Neural-Surrogate-for-Option-Pricing
items.description: This project develops neural-network surrogate models for fast, accurate European option pricing under stochastic volatility frameworks. Traditional methods like Monte Carlo simulations are computationally expensive. The goal is to use machine learning models, trained on synthetic data, for orders-of-magnitude faster pricing with similar accuracy.

items.name: Image-Text-Summarizer
items.description: Welcome to our Image to Text and Text to Summary Generation web application! This open-source project is built with Flask, a Python web framework, and leverages cutting-edge machine learning technologies to provide two essential functionalities in one place.

items.name: QUEST
items.description: A machine learning framework to generate quasar spectra

items.name: ml-mrsdalloway-intertextuality
items.description: A unified machine learning framework for thematic, emotional, and semantic analysis of Clarissa and Septimus narrative intertextuality in Mrs Dalloway.

items.name: counterfactual-ml-framework
items.description: Conceptual framework for counterfactual machine learning  bridging causal inference, AI ethics, and applied economics.

items.name: ml-demo
items.description: Unified Machine Learning/Deep Learning demo repository combining most of the popular ML frameworks.

items.name: StatML
items.description: Data augmentation, Machine learning, and Statistical analysis framework

items.name: Multilabel_Classification_with_Group_Testing_and_Codes
items.description: Implemented an efficient multilabel learning framework using Machine Learning Group Testing (MLGT). Designed code matrices via random construction and ReedSolomonbased methods, evaluated Precision@k vs. Hamming Loss, and optimized the training and prediction pipeline to achieve a 70% reduction in execution time compared to the One-vs-All model.

items.name: A-Cloud-Based-IoT-Framework-for-Comparative-Drinking-Water-Analysis-Using-Adaptive-AI-Models
items.description: This repository contains the full-stack code for a serverless, real-time water quality monitoring system. An ESP32 microcontroller sends sensor data (pH, turbidity, etc.) to a serverless backend on AWS, which processes the data, runs a machine learning model, stores it in DynamoDB. A dynamic web frontend then visualizes this data on a Leaflet map.

items.name: tensorflow-1762353883759
items.description: TensorFlow is an open-source machine learning framework developed by Google. It provides strong support for various platforms, especially Linux, and is widely adopted in the industry due to its active community and production-ready capabilities.

items.name: AetherAI
items.description: AetherAI is an open-source Python framework for evaluating, testing, and monitoring machine learning (ML) and large language model (LLM) systems  from experimentation to production. It helps you ensure data quality, detect drift, measure performance, and assess LLM outputs using 100+ built-in metrics and a modular dashboard.

items.name: ps-ppi
items.description: This repository is the official repository of the paper "A Unified Framework for Inference with General Missingness Patterns and Machine Learning Imputation".

items.name: Gait-Analysis
items.description: An angle calculator that is based on google's open source machine learning framework "mediapipe" that takes in a footage of a person walking and calculates different types of angles at each frame throughout the video. This is necessary for physicians to diagnose certain locomative related diseases.

items.name: titanic-survival-prediction
items.description: This project is a complete, end-to-end machine learning workflow to predict passenger survival from the famous Titanic dataset. The primary goal was to build a reliable classifier while mastering a repeatable framework for data cleaning, feature engineering, and model training.

items.name: esg-classification
items.description: A complete end-to-end framework for classifying corporate ESG performance using machine learning, SHAP, and interactive dashboards.

items.name: ml_genn_examples
items.description: Example scripts using the ml_genn machine learning framework for SNNs

items.name: Machine-Learning-Based-Prediction-of-Automobile-Prices-Using-Multivariate-Regression-Analysis
items.description: Developed a predictive modeling framework to estimate automobile prices using statistical and machine learning techniques.

items.name: credit_card_fraud_detection
items.description: A machine learning framework using Logistic Regression, Random Forest, and XGBoost to detect credit card fraud in real time. Built on the Kaggle dataset, it delivers scalable, explainable, and business-ready risk scoring for banks and financial institutions.

items.name: decision_modeling_framework
items.description: A reproducible framework for probabilistic decision modeling and simulation in high-volatility time series. Demonstrates how to use statistical indicators, machine learning classifiers, and automated workflows to test and evaluate data-driven decision rules under uncertainty.

items.name: Algorithmic-Empath-Human-Fallibility
items.description: A deep exploration of Algorithmic Empathy, the next frontier in AI understanding. This project examines how machines can learn from human fallibility, model disagreement, and align with moral reasoning. It blends psychology, fairness metrics, interpretability, and co-learning design into one framework for humane intelligence.

items.name: ML1-
items.description: This is a Python-based web application, built with the Flask framework, that serves as a Fertilizer Recommendation System. It uses a Decision Tree machine learning algorithm to predict the required fertilizer based on user-provided soil and crop data.

items.name: Project-I_GeneWise_Predictive_Modelling_for_Genetic_Disorders
items.description: GeneWise is a machine learning-based genomics project that predicts an individual's genetic disorder risk by analyzing Single Nucleotide Polymorphism (SNP) data. It combines data preprocessing, statistical feature selection, predictive modeling, and explainable Al (XAl) to deliver an accurate and interpretable framework for precision healthcare.

items.name: MediPredict-A-Unified-AI-Framework-for-Early-Diagnosis-of-Cardio-Pulmonary-and-Neuro-Disorders
items.description: It is an intelligent web-based disease prediction system designed to assist healthcare professionals and patients in identifying potential Heart, Lung, and Brain disorders using machine learning models.It provides an easy to use interface where users can input key health parameters, and the system predicts the disease occurrence with high accuracy.

items.name: xo-ai
items.description: Minimal Conversational Intelligence Framework with Memory & Reinforcement Learning

items.name: Steel-Plate-Fault-Classification-using-various-Machine-Learning-mode
items.description: Comparative study of machine learning classifiers (KNN, Weighted KNN, MLP) for industrial steel plate fault detection. Implements feature engineering with LDA/PCA dimensionality reduction, achieving 74% sensitivity and 96% specificity. Includes comprehensive data analysis, k-means clustering, and model evaluation framework.

items.name: Enwar1.0
items.description: Enwar is an LLM framework that processes multi-modal inputs, transforms them into textual representations, and in parallel pipelines that data to a set of machine learning models to complete specific tasks. Within this scope, the data inputs are pushed to a perception agent.

items.name: A-Hybrid-Ensemble-Forecasting-Framework-for-Olympic-Medal-Prediction
items.description: A Hybrid Ensemble Forecasting Framework for Olympic Medal Prediction: Integrating Panel Regression, Difference-in-Differences, and Machine Learning Approaches

items.name: fsds-generative-ai-agenti--ai
items.description: This repository documents my learning journey in Full Stack Data Science with a focus on Generative AI and Agentic AI. It includes daily tasks, hands-on projects, and experiments using Python, machine learning, and modern AI frameworks. The work reflects both foundational concepts and advanced techniques applied in real-world scenarios.

items.name: AIML-All-In-One-V1
items.description: A comprehensive AI project featuring machine learning model training, AI agent implementation using Microsoft Agent Framework, REST API, React UI, and Azure Development Kit evaluation with Docker deployment.

items.name: amiteshks
items.description: This repository serves as a hub for my ML/AI explorations, implementations, and tutorials. It includes:   Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) projects  Machine Learning models for predictions and classifications  Deep Learning projects using frameworks like TensorFlow, PyTorch, and Hugging Face  Natural Language Processing (NLP) applications

items.name: Predictive-Framework-for-Urban-Air-Quality
items.description: A machine learning framework to proactively forecast the Air Quality Index (AQI) in Indian cities using temporal feature engineering and a generalized XGBoost model.

items.name: InerLearn
items.description: InerLearn is a machine learning framework for autonomous IMU bias correction and self-localization without GPS. It combines classical and deep learning models to learn, predict, and compensate inertial sensor drift in realistic, physics-based simulations.

items.name: OECD-COMTOX
items.description: OECD Test Guidelines-based toxicity prediction using machine learning. Comprehensive computational toxicology framework with pre-trained models for genotoxicity, carcinogenicity, acute toxicity, DART, and ecotoxicity endpoints.

items.name: NeoMatrix
items.description: A rust powered machine learning framework for python

items.name: Cybersecurity-Suspicious-Web-Threat-Interactions
items.description: This project implements web threat analysis using both machine learning and deep learning techniques. It leverages a variety of libraries to preprocess data, build models, and evaluate their performance. The goal is to provide a robust framework for detecting and mitigating web-based threats such as malware, phishing, and other cybersecurity risks.

items.name: AutoHyperTune
items.description: A comprehensive repository for automatic hyperparameter tuning libraries, tools, and tutorials. This serves as a knowledge base for finding, comparing, and utilizing state-of-the-art hyperparameter optimization techniques to improve model performance across various machine learning frameworks.

items.name: MLJBase.jl
items.description: Core functionality for the MLJ machine learning framework

items.name: spatial-selectivity-estimation-ext
items.description: Framework for spatial selectivity estimation using machine learning and optimizer feedback. Addresses both RCC filters and distance-based filters by transforming estimation into regression task. Compares neural networks, tree-based models and instance-based approaches against traditional RTree and histogram methods across 14 spatial datasets.

items.name: Explainable-Credit-Risk-Modeling
items.description: This project demonstrates how explainable AI and machine learning can be used to build transparent credit risk models that satisfy regulatory requirements under Basel III, IFRS 9, and OSFI's E-23 guidelines. The framework provides comprehensive model interpretability using SHAP and LIME.

items.name: PyTorch
items.description: PyTorch is a fully featured framework for building deep learning models, which is a type of machine learning that's commonly used in applications like image recognition and language processing. Written in Python, it's relatively easy for most machine learning developers to learn and use.

items.name: Tywra-ML
items.description: Tywra ML is a front-end machine learning website built using the React.js library and the Next.js framework. This website was created as a simple project while also continuing advanced learning of JavaScript.

items.name: Federated-Learning-Hub
items.description: Privacy-preserving distributed machine learning framework that trains models across devices without sharing raw data - enterprise-grade federated AI.

items.name: Quantum-ML
items.description: Hybrid quantum-classical machine learning framework that runs on real quantum computers - bridge between quantum computing and AI.

items.name: spiking-learn
items.description: Framework for machine learning with spiking neural networks

items.name: ML_and_DL-algos
items.description: This repository contains all the machine learning and deep learning model I have implemented using various frameworks like keras, tensorflow, scikit-learn, pytorch, etc.

items.name: Sectoral-Analysis-of-Expected-Credit-Loss-in-Indian-Development-Finance-2014-2024-
items.description: Developed a machine learningbased framework to assess credit risk in World Bankfunded projects across India. Integrated financial and macroeconomic data to model PD, EAD, LGD, and ECL using CatBoost, applied SHAP for interpretability, and performed sectoral aggregation and stress testing for portfolio risk insights.

items.name: PORTFOLIO-OPTIMIZATION-with-blacklitterman-ESG-and-entropy
items.description: Portfolio Optimization is a data science project that creates investment portfolios to maximize returns and manage risk using mean-variance optimization and machine learning. It features customizable workflows and frameworks like PyPortfolioOpt, designed for finance students and early-career data scientists.

items.name: numpy-networks
items.description: A collection of neural network components implemented from scratch using only NumPy. This project focuses on deepening the understanding of machine learning theory by building everything manually without high-level frameworks.

items.name: diabetes-predictor-ml-flask
items.description: This project Diabetes Prediction System Using Machine Learning and Flask Web Framework, focuses on developing an intelligent web-based application to predict the likelihood of diabetes in individuals based on their medical parameters.

items.name: ShapeShift-Framework
items.description: ShapeShift is a hybrid physics-informed machine learning framework for efficient mechanical simulation of MEX 3D-printed parts. It transforms computationally expensive filament-level finite element models into fast and accurate solid surrogate models.

items.name: BRCATranstypia
items.description: BRCATranstypia: A machine learning framework for breast cancer PAM50 subtype prediction using TCGA-BRCA transcriptomic data. It integrates preprocessing, feature selection, model training (Random Forest, SVM, XGBoost), and visualization of gene expression patterns.

items.name: Automated-Diagnosis-of-Diabetic-Eye-Disorders-Using-Advanced-Deep-Learning-Techniques
items.description: Uva Wellassa University final year Research project witch made with machine learning and using Yolo and U-Net frameworks. The following was made to determine diabetic eye disorders using image processing.

items.name: Enhancing-USB-Security-A-MultiLayered-Framework-for-Detecting-Mitigating-BadUSB-Attacks
items.description: USB Guard is a multi-layered security framework that identifies hidden USB threats using behavioral analysis, power profiling, and machine learning. It merges cybersecurity and AI to detect BadUSB attacks, offering a smart, adaptive, and practical approach to modern device protection.

items.name: petastorm
items.description: Petastorm library enables single machine or distributed training and evaluation of deep learning models from datasets in Apache Parquet format. It supports ML frameworks such as Tensorflow, Pytorch, and PySpark and can be used from pure Python code.

items.name: DevFest2025
items.description: AI Innovation at Google DevFest ATL 2025 This repository showcases our AI project developed for Google DevFest Atlanta 2025. The project integrates machine learning, real-time data processing, and intelligent automation to solve real-world challenges through innovative use of Google Cloud AI and open-source frameworks.

items.name: Optimized-Multi-Model-Fusion-for-Accurate-Lung-Cancer-Prediction.
items.description: This project focuses on developing an optimized multi-model fusion approach to enhance the accuracy of lung cancer prediction using machine learning and deep learning techniques. By combining multiple models and optimizing their performance, the system aims to provide a more reliable and robust prediction framework for early lung cancer detection.

items.name: CogniThreat
items.description: A cutting-edge AI-driven network intrusion detection system that combines classical deep learning, quantum machine learning, probabilistic reasoning, and explainable AI into a unified framework.

items.name: AI-Framework
items.description: Python AI framework (running on both CPU and GPU) for machine learning and deep learning.

items.name: starml
items.description: sTarML: A Sequence-Based Machine Learning Framework for Predicting Bacterial sRNAmRNA Interactions

items.name: AIML
items.description: This repository contains a collection of AI and Machine Learning projects built using various libraries and frameworks such as TensorFlow, PyTorch, Scikit-learn, and others. It includes algorithms, models, and applications that demonstrate the power of machine learning and artificial intelligence to solve real-world problems.

items.name: MAJOR-PROJECT
items.description: only 350 not 450  This study developed a robust machine learning (ML) framework using miRNA expression data to accurately classify kidney cancer subtypes.

items.name: Flask
items.description: Flask is a lightweight, open-source Python web framework used in Data Science to deploy and manage data-driven applications. It offers a simple yet powerful structure for creating web apps and APIs that integrate with data analysis or machine learning models, providing flexibility for custom solutions.

items.name: LibrasRealTime
items.description: O `LibrasRealTime`  um projeto de Viso Computacional em tempo real que visa explorar e aplicar tcnicas de Machine Learning e Deep Learning para a deteco de gestos do alfabeto LIBRAS. Desenvolvido em Python, o projeto utiliza bibliotecas lderes da indstria como OpenCV para captura e processamento de imagens e o framework MediaPipe.

items.name: EUR-Rates-ML-Backtester
items.description: Machine learningdriven backtesting framework for EUR 10-year rates, featuring intraday TP/SL execution, walk-forward modelling, and performance analytics.

items.name: cybershield_2.0
items.description: CyberShield - Advanced penetration testing framework. Features blockchain security, IoT device discovery, cloud misconfiguration detection, API security testing, and social engineering analysis with machine learning risk assessment.

items.name: Semi-Supervised-ML-Framework_For_Flood_Prediction
items.description: Semi-supervised machine learning framework for datasets with limited labels, demonstrating applied AI/ML and data science skills in predictive modeling. Includes rigorous data preprocessing, selective pseudo-labeling, and a three-phase training workflow, achieving strong result of test F1 = 0.9986, surpassing published benchmarks

items.name: -UC-Irvine-Machine-Learning-
items.description: UC Irvine Machine Learning  dataset for(Privacy-Preserving Machine Learning Framework)

items.name: PIML
items.description: This project develops a hybrid, interpretable framework that integrates physics-based resistance-capacitance (RC) models with machine learning regression algorithms to predict indoor thermal dynamics in buildings. The workflow demonstrates how domain knowledge can be embedded within data-driven models to enhance interpretability and accuracy

items.name: Hybrid-Explainable-Framework-for-Stroke-Prediction
items.description: AI-powered system for early stroke prediction that combines machine learning, deep learning, and explainable AI techniques. This comprehensive framework enhances predictive accuracy while ensuring clinical interpretability and fairness in healthcare applications.

items.name: How-Streamlit-Makes-AI-Accessible
items.description: A detailed educational article exploring how Streamlit revolutionizes AI app development. Learn how this Python framework bridges the gap between data science and usability, empowering anyone to deploy interactive machine learning models without front-end coding or complex infrastructure.

items.name: mlcolvar
items.description: A unified framework for machine learning collective variables for enhanced sampling simulations

items.name: The-Lord-of-The-Words-The-two-frameworks
items.description: Translation exploration with Transformers and Machine Learning Experimentation Platfroms

items.name: NNBrain
items.description: A high-performance neural network plugin for Godot 4.x, powered by Rust and Candle ML framework. Add real-time machine learning capabilities to your games with easy-to-use Brain nodes.

items.name: SANN
items.description: Enhancing Malignant Transformation Predictions in Oral Potentially Malignant Disorders: A Novel Machine Learning Framework Using Real-World Data

items.name: julia
items.description: Machine Learning Framework

items.name: fuse
items.description: A simple minimalistic machine learning framework for C++

items.name: BUILD-AND-DEPLOY-MACHINE-LEARNING-APPLICATIONS
items.description: Focuses on ML application design, using frameworks for Windows-based web apps. Covers APIs, Flask, and Docker for deploying ML models. Students gain hands-on experience in building scalable and production-ready ML systems.

items.name: DeepGNN
items.description: DeepGNN is a framework for training machine learning models on large scale graph data.

items.name: __nfl-betting-model-v1
items.description: PROBABLY THE BEST VERSION - Data-Driven Predictions for NFL Games and Player Props  This repository contains a modular, end-to-end machine learning framework for predicting NFL game outcomes, point spreads, and player prop performances using historical team and player data.

items.name: DeepForge
items.description: Advanced multi-model deepfake detection framework combining ensemble machine learning with deep neural networks for robust image authentication and media forensics.

items.name: stress-level-classification-nlp-ml
items.description: An experimental project integrating NLP and Machine Learning classification models to identify and categorize stress levels from text data  developed based on the Machine Learning Life Cycle (MLLC) framework.

items.name: StrokeAssist
items.description: Code repository for the publication "STROKE-ASSIST: a novel machine learning framework for stroke type identification in resource-constrained settings resilient to missing data"

items.name: AsTRiQue
items.description: ASk The RIght QUEstions: An active machine learning framework for perception experiments

items.name: machine_learning_1_framework
items.description: Code framework used during postgrad school for machine learning modeling

items.name: eclipsera
items.description: A machine learning framework built from scratch with 68 algorithms spanning classical ML, clustering, dimensionality reduction, manifold learning, AutoML, and explainability.

items.name: AIxOps-Engineer
items.description: AIxOps Engineering is a unified framework for MLOps, LLMOps, and AIOps. It provides end-to-end pipelines, best practices, and tools to build, deploy, monitor, and scale machine learning models, large language models, and AI-driven systems, enabling streamlined AI lifecycle management across diverse environments.

items.name: Machine-Learning---Deep-Learning-project
items.description: A collection of hands-on machine learning and deep learning projects, including image classification, text classification, and summarization with modern frameworks (TensorFlow, PyTorch, HuggingFace)

items.name: awesome-machine-learning
items.description: A curated list of awesome Machine Learning frameworks, libraries and software.

items.name: Multimodal-Machine-Learning-and-Data-Analysis-Framework-for-Depression-Detection
items.description: Master's thesis codebase for evaluation of fusion strategies in clinical depression screening. Multimodal depression detection framework using Text, Audio, and Video modalities with Early and Late Fusion strategies. Implements Logistic Regression and XGBoost classifiers on E-DAIC dataset with SHAP and coefficient-based methods.

items.name: aida
items.description: AIDA (Analysis and Intervention in the context of a Dropout Alerts) -- an explainable machine learning framework for detecting student disengagement and predicting dropout risk in higher education through quiz interaction analysis.
